<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-471] tunefs.lustre documentation with faulty example</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-471</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have discovered an error in the current lustre documentation describing tunefs.lustre. the example given in chapter 44.17.4 is incorrect, after &quot;--erase-param&quot; should follow the parameter to erase, in this case &quot;mgsnode&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the given example in the documentation did not work on a lustre 2.10.3 installation, while the following line did:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
tunefs.lustre --erase-param mgsnode --mgsnode=new_nid --writeconf /dev/sda&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;also, in 44.17.3, the --erase-param option is missing, I&apos;d recommend to add the wording from the man page.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>CentOS 7.3, Lustre 2.10.3</environment>
        <key id="59345">LUDOC-471</key>
